"},{"from":"da","to":"dad","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"m","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"m","to":"ma","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"ma","to":"mad","highlight":"muted"}]},"pat":{"type":"array1d","cells":[{"key":"c0","value":".","pointers":[]},{"key":"c1","value":"a","pointers":[]},{"key":"c2","value":"d","pointers":["idx"]}],"range":null}}},{"line":23,"caption":"Search(\".ad\") returns true (matched via \"bad\"). The d- and m-branches the dot opened are never tried — short-circuit.","note":"Any single matching branch makes the whole Search return true. The leading dot opened three branches {b, d, m}; the first one (bad) reached an `IsEnd` node, so the answer is true and the rest are pruned. Had no branch reached an `IsEnd` node — e.g. Search(\".a\") with only three-letter words stored — every branch would return false and so would Search.","vars":{"stored":"[bad, dad, mad]","query":".ad","idx":3,"node":"'bad'","branch":"b","node.IsEnd":true,"result":true},"result":true,"states":{"trie":{"type":"graph","directed":true,"nodes":[{"key":"root","value":"root","x":50,"y":8,"highlight":"path"},{"key":"b","value":"b","x":20,"y":34,"highlight":"path"},{"key":"d","value":"d","x":50,"y":34,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"m","value":"m","x":80,"y":34,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ba","value":"a","x":20,"y":60,"highlight":"path"},{"key":"da","value":"a","x":50,"y":60,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"ma","value":"a","x":80,"y":60,"highlight":"muted"},{"key":"bad","value":"bad*","x":20,"y":86,"highlight":"match"},{"key":"dad","value":"dad*","x":50,"y":86,"highlight":"visited"},{"key":"mad","value":"mad*","x":80,"y":86,"highlight":"visited"}],"edges":[{"from":"root","to":"b","highlight":"path"},{"from":"b","to":"ba","highlight":"path"},{"from":"ba","to":"bad","highlight":"path"},{"from":"root","to":"d","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"d","to":"da","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"da","to":"dad","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"root","to":"m","highlight":"muted"},{"from":"m","to":"ma","h